    "back": "Formal ('thin') conception (Dicey, Raz): (1) government must act according to law, not arbitrary power; (2) all persons are equal before the law; (3) the law must be clear, prospective, stable, and publicly promulgated. Substantive ('thick') conception (Bingham, Dworkin): the rule of law also requires that laws respect fundamental rights and substantive justice — formal legality alone is not enough. Lord Bingham (The Rule of Law, 2010) proposed eight sub-rules including access to justice, clear and accessible law, and protection of human rights.",
