    "back": "Jeremy Waldron (Dignity, Rank, and Rights, 2012) argues that modern human dignity is the extension of high-ranking status (once reserved for nobles) to every human being — a 'levelling up' of rank. Dignity is the foundational value underlying human rights: it explains why rights are universal, inalienable, and cannot be traded away. Dignity features in the UDHR (Art 1), the German Basic Law (Art 1), and increasingly in common law jurisprudence as a value informing the interpretation of rights.",
